OL,3,CEngland's men facing silent health
OL,4,Ccrisis, councils warn
OL,6,FA report by the body ` Men's health:
OL,7,FThe lives of men in our communities `
OL,8,Fclaims men in deprived areas live up
OL,9,Fto 10 years less than counterparts in
OL,10,Fwealthy areas, with smoking and
OL,11,Fexcessive alcohol consumption
OL,12,Fcontributing factors to the gap.
OL,14,FDavid Fothergill, chairman of the
OL,15,FLGA's community wellbeing board, said:
OL,16,F"Men in England are facing a silent
OL,17,Fhealth crisis, dying nearly four years
OL,18,Fearlier than women with high rates of
OL,19,Fcancers, heart disease, type 2
OL,20,Fdiabetes, and suicides.
