OL,3,CEngland's men facing silent health
OL,4,Ccrisis, councils warn
OL,6,F"Stark inequalities mean men in
OL,7,Fdeprived areas live almost 10 years
OL,8,Fless than their more affluent peers."
OL,10,FKaren Tyrell, chief executive of the
OL,11,Fcharity Drinkaware, added: "Our
OL,12,Fresearch shows that 28% of male
OL,13,Fdrinkers regularly drink above the
OL,14,Fchief medical officer's guidelines of
OL,15,F14 units per week, compared to 12% of
OL,16,Fwomen.
OL,18,F"This is putting men's health at risk,
OL,19,Fand we need to reduce that number."
